<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870818-0036 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Geotech Energy Corp.</HL><DD> 08/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> PETROLEUM (PET) </IN><TEXT>   Geotech Energy Corp. said it expects to drill at least 20 additional oil wells and triple its oil production in the 1987 second half.    Michael G. Reedy, president of the Houston-based oil company, said: &quot;We're looking for a big increase in drilling in the second half of this year. With higher prices, more stability, and a lot more confidence in the marketplace, I see a 200% increase in our drilling projects. That means we will be drilling at least 20 more wells this year.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>